<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 13:00:43 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>巴兹·奥尔德林使用这支简陋的毡尖笔拯救了阿波罗二号宇航员。它刚刚以超过 850,000 美元的价格售出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/buzz-aldrin-used-this-humble-felt-tip-pen-to-save-the-apollo-ii-astronauts-it-just-sold-for-more-than-850000-180989142/</link><description>1969年7月，思维敏捷的奥尔德林在登月过程中开关断开后，用书写工具重新启动了登月舱“鹰”的发动机臂电路。</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 21:22:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/buzz-aldrin-used-this-humble-felt-tip-pen-to-save-the-apollo-ii-astronauts-it-just-sold-for-more-than-850000-180989142/</guid></item><item><title>这艘维京长船在克里斯托弗·诺兰的《奥德赛》中横渡大西洋，饰演奥德修斯的希腊桨帆船</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thisviking-longship-crossed-the-atlantic-before-starring-in-christopher-nolans-odyssey-as-odysseus-greek-galley-180989137/</link><description>马特·达蒙等好莱坞明星前往赛艇训练营学习如何为新电影操作船只</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 20:27:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thisviking-longship-crossed-the-atlantic-before-starring-in-christopher-nolans-odyssey-as-odysseus-greek-galley-180989137/</guid></item><item><title>这颗陨石于 2024 年坠入新泽西州的一处住宅。现在，科学家称它包含一些生命的组成部分</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-meteorite-crashed-into-a-new-jersey-home-in-2024-now-scientists-say-it-contains-some-of-the-building-blocks-of-life-180989138/</link><description>根据一项新的研究，希尔斯伯勒陨石属于一类罕见的太空岩石。它含有氨基酸和其他有机化合物，以及咸水的证据</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 20:04:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-meteorite-crashed-into-a-new-jersey-home-in-2024-now-scientists-say-it-contains-some-of-the-building-blocks-of-life-180989138/</guid></item><item><title>白金汉宫皇家美术馆恢复沙龙式展览，展出的杰作数量增加了一倍</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/buckingham-palaces-royal-picture-gallery-revives-the-salon-style-hang-doubling-the-number-of-masterpieces-on-view-180989135/</link><description>据报道，查理三世在风格转变中拥有发言权，重新排列并添加了伦勃朗、鲁本斯、维米尔和范戴克等人的艺术作品</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 18:13:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/buckingham-palaces-royal-picture-gallery-revives-the-salon-style-hang-doubling-the-number-of-masterpieces-on-view-180989135/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，智能手机可能是美国出生率下降的原因之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/smartphones-might-be-playing-a-role-in-the-united-states-declining-birth-rate-new-research-suggests-180989129/</link><description>一些经济学家怀疑，该技术的广泛采用减少了面对面的互动，增加了获取色情内容和节育信息的机会，从而减少了无保护的性行为</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:05:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/smartphones-might-be-playing-a-role-in-the-united-states-declining-birth-rate-new-research-suggests-180989129/</guid></item><item><title>男子因使用化名、假身份证和假手稿窃取价值超过 20 万美元的“稀有且独特”的中文文本而被判刑</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/man-sentenced-for-stealing-rare-and-unique-chinese-texts-valued-at-more-than-200000-by-using-aliases-fake-ids-and-dummy-manuscripts-180989134/</link><description>这些作品在几年的时间里从加州大学洛杉矶分校被盗</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 15:18:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/man-sentenced-for-stealing-rare-and-unique-chinese-texts-valued-at-more-than-200000-by-using-aliases-fake-ids-and-dummy-manuscripts-180989134/</guid></item><item><title>长颈鹿可能比我们想象的还要聪明。一项新研究表明，有些可以解决简单的数学问题</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/giraffes-might-be-even-smarter-than-we-thought-some-can-solve-simple-math-problems-a-new-study-suggests-180989124/</link><description>四只接受测试的长颈鹿中的两只似乎能够在头脑中组合数字以获得它们最喜欢的食物之一：胡萝卜。但所有动物都未能完成涉及减法或多重计算的任务</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/giraffes-might-be-even-smarter-than-we-thought-some-can-solve-simple-math-problems-a-new-study-suggests-180989124/</guid></item><item><title>曾经是世界上最大的客轮，这艘跨越大西洋并将移民带到澳大利亚的金属奇迹拥有了新的博物馆</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/once-the-worlds-biggest-passenger-ship-this-metal-marvel-the-ss-great-britain-that-crossed-the-atlantic-and-took-immigrants-to-australia-has-a-new-museum-home-180989130/</link><description>一座专门展示 SS“大不列颠”号故事的新博物馆即将在布里斯托尔开放，该船永久停泊在干船坞中</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:34:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/once-the-worlds-biggest-passenger-ship-this-metal-marvel-the-ss-great-britain-that-crossed-the-atlantic-and-took-immigrants-to-australia-has-a-new-museum-home-180989130/</guid></item><item><title>科学家根据奔跑速度对数百种蜘蛛进行了排名。澳大利亚体型巨大、毛茸茸的棕色猎人名列前茅</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-ranked-hundreds-of-spider-species-by-running-speed-australias-huge-hairy-brown-huntsman-came-out-on-top-180989132/</link><description>棕色猎人的冲刺速度最高可达每小时八英里，但它只能保持这个速度不到一秒钟。该研究将有助于更好地了解蜘蛛的进化和生物力学</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:02:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-ranked-hundreds-of-spider-species-by-running-speed-australias-huge-hairy-brown-huntsman-came-out-on-top-180989132/</guid></item><item><title>天文学家注意到望远镜图像中出现了一个神秘的斑点。事实证明，它是地球上拍摄到的最暗的系外行星</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronomers-noticed-a-mysterious-spot-appearing-in-telescope-images-it-turned-out-to-be-the-faintest-exoplanet-ever-imaged-from-earth-180989133/</link><description>这颗名为 Beta Pictoris d 的气态巨行星十多年来一直隐藏在人们的视线中，直到两个独立团队证实了它的存在</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 19:40:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronomers-noticed-a-mysterious-spot-appearing-in-telescope-images-it-turned-out-to-be-the-faintest-exoplanet-ever-imaged-from-earth-180989133/</guid></item><item><title>人工智能音乐已经来了。为了保护人类艺术家，唱片业提出新标签，例如露骨歌词的标签</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ai-music-is-already-here-to-protect-human-artists-the-record-industry-proposes-labels-for-it-like-those-for-explicit-lyrics-180989128/</link><description>这项提议提出之际，人工智能生成的音乐在流媒体平台上的可用内容中所占的份额越来越大</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 18:47:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ai-music-is-already-here-to-protect-human-artists-the-record-industry-proposes-labels-for-it-like-those-for-explicit-lyrics-180989128/</guid></item><item><title>古埃及人相信这些新发现的金舌头可以让死者在来世进行交流</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ancient-egyptians-believed-that-these-newly-discovered-gold-tongues-allowed-the-dead-to-communicate-in-the-afterlife-180989127/</link><description>在亚历山大以西的Marina el-Alamein考古遗址进行的挖掘工作中，出土了大约两打稀有文物，其中包括一件形状像荷鲁斯之眼的文物</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 17:31:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ancient-egyptians-believed-that-these-newly-discovered-gold-tongues-allowed-the-dead-to-communicate-in-the-afterlife-180989127/</guid></item><item><title>科学家首次实时目睹海底扩张，让他们罕见地一睹神秘的地质过程</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-scientists-witness-the-seafloor-spread-in-real-time-giving-them-a-rare-glimpse-at-a-mysterious-geologic-process-180989123/</link><description>一项新研究显示，2024 年短短几天内，印度洋部分地区的海底下降了约 13 英尺，约 57 亿立方英尺的熔岩上升到地壳表面</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 16:02:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-scientists-witness-the-seafloor-spread-in-real-time-giving-them-a-rare-glimpse-at-a-mysterious-geologic-process-180989123/</guid></item><item><title>天文学家首次在恒星之间的空间中发现了糖，为地球生命起源提供了新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-astronomers-find-sugar-in-the-space-between-stars-providing-new-clues-about-the-origins-of-life-on-earth-180989122/</link><description>糖是 RNA 和 DNA 的重要组成部分，是当今所有已知生物体的基础。在一项新的研究中，在银河系中心附近充满气体和灰尘的云中检测到了糖赤藓酮糖</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-astronomers-find-sugar-in-the-space-between-stars-providing-new-clues-about-the-origins-of-life-on-earth-180989122/</guid></item><item><title>这块霸王龙化石的拍卖价格可能是有史以来拍卖价格最高的恐龙。科学家担心他们会失去研究它的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</link><description>“Gus”的起价为 1900 万美元，这对于公共机构来说是一个很高的价格。私人收藏的标本对于研究人员来说更难检查，而且它们实际上不可能包含在顶级科学期刊的研究中</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</guid></item><item><title>来认识一下 Sak Tahn Waax，一位生活在 1000 多年前的玛雅数学奇才，留下了一个“非常优雅、复杂”的公式</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-sak-tahn-waax-a-maya-math-whiz-who-lived-more-than-1000-years-ago-and-left-behind-a-really-elegant-complex-formula-180989125/</link><description>考古学家首次确认了该文化中一位著名的古典时代数学家和天文学家的身份</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 13:03:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-sak-tahn-waax-a-maya-math-whiz-who-lived-more-than-1000-years-ago-and-left-behind-a-really-elegant-complex-formula-180989125/</guid></item><item><title>英国国王的尸骨被移动了几个世纪，最终丢失了。一位研究人员声称他发现了它们的位置——在停车场下面</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-kings-bones-were-moved-over-centuries-and-eventually-lost-one-researcher-claims-he-discovered-their-location-under-a-parking-lot-180989121/</link><description>阿尔弗雷德大帝保卫威塞克斯免受维京人的侵害。在修道院的安息地被扰乱后，研究人员多年来一直在寻找他的遗骸</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 20:37:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-kings-bones-were-moved-over-centuries-and-eventually-lost-one-researcher-claims-he-discovered-their-location-under-a-parking-lot-180989121/</guid></item><item><title>这些可爱的老鼠是如何在没有其他哺乳动物居住的极高海拔地区生活的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-how-these-adorable-mice-can-live-at-an-extremely-high-elevation-where-no-other-mammal-is-known-to-survive-180989116/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，安第斯叶耳鼠具有适应能力，可以帮助其在海拔 22,000 英尺的寒冷、低氧条件下有效地产生体温</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:45:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-how-these-adorable-mice-can-live-at-an-extremely-high-elevation-where-no-other-mammal-is-known-to-survive-180989116/</guid></item><item><title>这座拥有 700 年历史的英国教堂差点关闭，但随后牧师在祭坛下发现了藏匿的金币</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-700-year-old-english-church-nearly-closed-but-then-the-vicar-discovered-a-stash-of-gold-coins-under-the-altar-180989120/</link><description>复活节前夕，一盒 20 世纪 90 年代铸造的金条改变了一小群正在努力支付昂贵维修费用的会众的前景</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:26:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-700-year-old-english-church-nearly-closed-but-then-the-vicar-discovered-a-stash-of-gold-coins-under-the-altar-180989120/</guid></item><item><title>罗马混凝土是如何延续千年的？拥有 1,900 年历史的厕所提供了有关该材料令人印象深刻的耐用性的新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-has-roman-concrete-lasted-for-millennia-a-1900-year-old-latrine-offers-new-clues-about-the-materials-impressive-durability-180989115/</link><description>一种称为碳化的化学过程有助于密封裂缝，这有助于解释为什么许多古罗马建筑至今仍屹立不倒。研究人员希望这些见解能够带来更好的现代建筑材料</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 15:54:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-has-roman-concrete-lasted-for-millennia-a-1900-year-old-latrine-offers-new-clues-about-the-materials-impressive-durability-180989115/</guid></item></channel></rss>